comment._content: 29 July 1943: WWI ace "Captain Eddie" Rickenbacker pays a visit to the 56th FG at Halesworth - and may have witnessed P-47C serial 41-6342 (coded LM-D) making this belly-landing as a result of battle damage. The ship was normally assigned to CAPT Ray Dauphin of the 62nd Fighter Squadron, nicknamed 'Saucy Shirley.'
